25/06/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian President Boris Tadic will start a regional tour Monday (26 June), with stops in Montenegro, Croatia, Macedonia and Bosnia and Herzegovina. The visit to Podgorica will be his first since the dissolution of the former state union and the proclamation of Montenegro as an independent state. Tadic will meet with his Montenegrin counterpart, Filip Vujanovic, and Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic. 
In other news, Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica confirmed on Friday that he and Tadic have obtained an invitation from US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice to visit Washington next month. Frank Wisner, the US envoy for the Kosovo status talks, told the Voice of America that the invitation is an expression of respect towards the Serbian leaders and Serbian democratic institutions. (RTS - 25/06/06; Beta, Blic - 24/06/06; B92 - 23/06/06)
